Using the Compiler
------------------

1. Example

The command 'satk filename.sa' will produce the assembly 'filename.exe' if the
main class has the name FILENAME. This assembly could be executed by the command
'mono filename.exe'.

2. Options

satk [-m classname] [-o file] [-il] [-l] sourcefile

-m classname : sets the name of the main class
-o file      : output filename
-il          : generate IL-Code
-l           : long error output (untested)

3. Compiling multiple files

At this time this is only possible by piping:

cat file1.sa file2.sa ... | satk

4. Reporting Bugs

Please report bugs to:
maik.schoepe@informatik.uni-halle.de
